\begin_layout ExampleBlock
Because 
\begin_inset Formula $Y=X^{2}$
\end_inset

 is always positive 
\begin_inset Formula $F_{Y}(y)=0$
\end_inset

 whenever 
\begin_inset Formula $y\leq0$
\end_inset

.
 When 
\begin_inset Formula $y>0$
\end_inset

 it follows 
\begin_inset Formula $Y\leqslant y\Leftrightarrow-\sqrt{y}\leqslant X\leqslant\sqrt{y}$
\end_inset

 so that 
\begin_inset Formula $F_{Y}(y)=F_{X}(\sqrt{y})-F_{X}(-\sqrt{y})$
\end_inset

.
 If the random variable 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 has a density function we can differentiate the last expression to obtain
 the density function of 
\begin_inset Formula $Y$
\end_inset

:
\begin_inset Formula \[
f_{Y}(y)=\begin{cases}
\frac{1}{2\sqrt{y}}\left[f_{X}(\sqrt{y})+f_{X}(-\sqrt{y})\right], & y>0,\\
0, & \mbox{otherwise.}\end{cases}\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

